Pepperoni and cheese calzones made with Rao’s Homemade Marinara Sauce are a MUST! To add some spice, you can use Rao’s Homemade Arrabbiata sauce, but either way these are 

 #RaosPartner #MakeEveryDayDelicious
 
Ingredients:
1 lb store bought or homemade dough
Flour
1 lb shredded low-moisture mozzarella cheese 
1/2 lb- 1 lb pepperoni
Garlic salt
Olive oil 
Oregano for garnish
Rao’s Homemade Marinara or Arrabbiata Sauce, for dipping 
 
 
Instructions:
•preheat oven to 425 degrees
•take dough out of refrigerator 3 hours before cooking and allow to rise 
•Roll out rough with a tiny bit of flour. Don’t use too much or over handle the dough 
•make shape of long rectangle, about 5 inches wide and 2 feet long but this can vary
•place cheese and mozzarella along the center of the dough, leaving about 1-2 inches of dough on either side 
•fold dough at both ends of the calzone and then fold excess dough on the sides to meet in the middle to create the calzone shape. Pinch very carefully to make sure there are no holes in dough!!!! You want to make sure there’s no saucy overflow as it cooks  
•coat pan with olive oil  
•place calzone pleated seam-side down on pan
•sprinkle with garlic salt
•cook for 20-30 minutes or until golden brown
•while cooking calzone, heat Rao’s Homemade Sauce on low heat, stirring until a light simmer
•place in bowl and garnish with oregano
•take out calzone, cut into finger pieces for serving (or don’t, do you hunni!) enjoy

What exactly is #endometriosis? 

It’s a disease where tissue that resembles the lining of the uterus is present outside of the uterus. It causes chronic inflammation and scarring leading to pain and/or infertility. It’s a complex disease and affects so many women around the world - starting with their first period all the way through menopause if not treated properly. 

Symptoms include:
•Painful periods that affect your ability to do the things you want to do 
•Chronic pelvic/vaginal/rectal/abdominal/hips/back pain 
•Fatigue 
•Abdominal bloating 
•Infertility
•Nausea 
•Pain during or after sex 
•Painful bowel movements and urination 

I found so much comfort in the stories of other women when I didn’t have the answers and it’s been an honor to pay it forward. I hope by sharing this I can support someone feeling isolated and misunderstood in their pain, as so many women with endometriosis feel. The average diagnosis for endometriosis is 10 years

Here are some things I wish I knew 15 years ago before I knew about endo

* Advocate for your health. SEEK help and demand answers, even if that means switching doctors 
* Painful periods are not nornal
* Do your own research
* Find support in your community or online forums 
* Don’t be embarrassed to speak up about your symptoms. You’re not alone and you are more than 1 in 10💛

I never wanted to say out loud I have rectovaginal endometriosis, even to close friends and family, because I was embarrassed. It’s raw. But if I can help one person out there get the answers they need and the strength to speak up for their health, then I’ll talk about my experience all day long. So here it is 💛💛 thank you so much @endofound for this special award and to my fellow honoree @corinnefoxx for all that you do

If you’re like me and your biggest fear on earth is anything happening to your parents or loved ones @Prenuvo is an incredible preventative tool that provides life saving information to proactively keep everyone’s health on track. Also this is not an ad but something I wanted to share because I know it can save someone’s life.🌟The healthcare system today can be reactive and slow to diagnose disease, leading to poor health outcomes for many diagnosed conditions. Prenuvo uses advanced MRI to perform a preventive scan, able to detect solid cancerous tumors at stage 1 and around 500 other conditions (including aneurysms, spine herniations, musculoskeletal conditions, fatty liver disease etc). Unlike other screening mechanisms, Prenuvo does not use radiation or contrast, making it a safe preventative screening tool. On average, Prenuvo gives potentially life-saving insights to 1/20 people. The vast majority of cancers (and medical conditions) found are at a very early stage, and occur in mostly asymptomatic patients.
